This paper is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) sub-category as it focuses on malware detection and security of information systems. The use of machine learning algorithms such as Graph Matching Networks also suggests that it could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the behavior-based approach to malware detection, which could place it in the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category. Finally, the use of graph modeling and similarity metrics could also suggest that it belongs to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
